<div>
    <center>
<h1>Easy Bourbon Chicken</h1>
        <hr>
    </center>
</div>
    <center>
<h2>Easy Bourbon Chicken that's crispy, sweet, sticky and tastes just like the kind you grew up eating at the mall!  </h2>
    </center>

<div>
<center>
<img src="pictures/Bourbon.png"
</center>
</div>

<div>

<h3>Ingridients:</h3>
<ul>
    <li>▢5-6 skinless boneless chicken breasts - about 3 pounds</li>
    <li>▢3 tablespoons cornstarch divided</li>
    <li>▢1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
    <li>▢1/4 teaspoon black pepper</li>
    <li>▢4 tablespoons canola oil</li>
    <li>▢2 cloves garlic minced</li>
    <li>▢1 cup water</li>
    <li>▢1/2 cup apple juice</li>
    <li>▢1/4 cup bourbon</li>
    <li>▢1/2 cup chicken broth</li>
    <li>▢2/3 cup lite soy sauce lower sodium</li>
    <li>▢1/3 cup ketchup</li>
    <li>▢2 tablespoons apple cider vinegar</li>
    <li>▢1 cup packed light brown sugar</li>
    <li>▢1/2 teaspoon onion powder</li>
    <li>▢1/2 teaspoon ground ginger</li>
    <li>▢1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes</li>
</ul>

</div>


<h3>Instructions:</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Cut the chicken into 1 inch pieces and in a large bowl toss it with 2 tablespoons of the cornstarch, salt, and pepper.</li>
    <li>Add 2 tablespoons of canola oil into your nonstick skillet on medium high heat and let it heat until adding the first piece of chicken sizzles.</li>
    <li>Add half the chicken pieces and cook for 3 minutes without stirring.</li>
    <li>Turn the chicken pieces and cook and additional three minutes.</li>
    <li>Remove the chicken from the pan.</li>
    <li>Use the remaining oil to cook the second half of the chicken the same way.</li>
    <li>Remove the chicken from the pan.</li>
    <li>Add in the garlic and cook for 20 seconds until you can just smell it.</li>
    <li>Add in the water, apple juice, bourbon, chicken broth, lite soy sauce, ketchup, apple cider vinegar, brown sugar, onion powder, ground ginger and red pepper flakes.</li>
    <li>Bring to a boil then add back in the chicken.</li>
    <li>Cook for 10-15 minutes or until the sauce is reduced by about half.</li>
    <li>Add the remaining tablespoon of cornstarch to a small glass with a tablespoon of water and stir.</li>
    <li>Add into the pan and stir.</li>
    <li>Cook until the sauce is thickened. Serve immediately.</li>

</ol>



